# KiCad Shortcuts

## General (all editors)
# Undo / Redo
Ctrl+z / Ctrl+y

# Zoom in / out
Scroll wheel (or +/-)

# Zoom to fit
Home

# Zoom to selection
Ctrl+F5

# Pan
Middle-click drag (or Shift+scroll)

# Properties
e

# Delete
Del

# Duplicate
Ctrl+d

# Find
Ctrl+f / t (next match)

# Preferences
Ctrl+,

# Hotkey list
Ctrl+F1

## Schematic Editor
# Place symbol
a

# Place power symbol
p

# Place wire
w

# Place bus
b

# Place label / global label
l / Ctrl+l

# Place no-connect flag
q

# Place junction
j

# Move (break wires)
m

# Drag (keep wires attached)
g

# Rotate / Mirror X / Mirror Y
r / x / y

# Copy
c

# Edit symbol value
v

# Edit symbol reference
u

# Edit symbol footprint
f

# Annotate schematic
(menu) Tools → Annotate

# Run ERC
(menu) Inspect → Electrical Rules Checker

# Generate netlist / BOM
(menu) Tools → Generate Netlist / BOM

# Update PCB from schematic
F8

## PCB Editor
# Route single track
x

# Route differential pair
d (in route mode)

# Drag track (keep connections)
d

# Move item
m

# Rotate / Flip to other side
r / f

# Change track width
w

# Switch active layer (while routing)
v

# Select active layer
Page Up / Page Down

# Add via (while routing)
v

# Add filled zone
Ctrl+Shift+z

# Fill all zones / Unfill all zones
b / Ctrl+b

# Select net inspector
n (in selection)

# Highlight net
` (backtick)

# Clear highlight
Esc

# Inspect clearance
i

# Measure tool
Ctrl+Shift+m

# Toggle board layers visibility
(click in Layers panel)

# Toggle ratsnest
(menu) View → Ratsnest

# Run DRC
(menu) Inspect → Design Rules Checker

# 3D Viewer
Alt+3

# Update schematic from PCB
(menu) Tools → Update Schematic from PCB

# Interactive router settings
< / > (decrease/increase corner rounding)

## Footprint Editor
# Place pad
(menu) Place → Pad

# Edit pad properties
e (on pad)

# Set grid origin
s

## Selection
# Select item
Click

# Add to selection
Shift+click

# Select all
Ctrl+a

# Filter selection
(right-click) → Select → Filter

# Select connected tracks
u (expand selection)
